  "texts": [
    "The Area Under the Curve (AUC) quantifies discriminative power, with higher values indicating superior performance.",
    "AUC values near 1 signify a perfect classifier, while 0.5 suggests random guessing.",
    "This metric is valuable for evaluating classifiers on imbalanced datasets, ensuring a thorough assessment in multi-classification tasks.The LLAMA2 models, as illustrated in Table I, display a strong performance across accuracy, F1-score, and ROC-AUC, indicating their robust ability in emergency situation classification.",
    "The LLAMA2-70B model, in particular, excels, showcasing its strength in nuanced language processing.",
    "Conversely, the Mistral models, despite lower accuracy, show high F1 and ROC-AUC scores, suggesting effectiveness in identifying true positives over various thresholds."
